headline: TransDigm Group (TDG) Sees Sales And Net Income Growth In Q3 Earnings
summary: TransDigm Group (TDG) recently provided earnings guidance for FY 2025, projecting net sales and income increases, with EPS expected to rise significantly. Over the last quarter, the company's price moved 1% while experiencing a series of key events. This includes Q3 earnings results showing year-over-year sales and net income growth, a share buyback update, and strategic index reassignments. These developments provided positive context amid a generally positive stock market backdrop, where...
